====== H4682: מַצָּה (matstsâh) ======

===== Source =====

from  H4711  in the sense of   devouring for sweetness;

===== Meaning =====

greedily properly,  sweetness ; concretely,  sweet  (i.e. not soured or bittered with yeast); specifically, an  unfermented cake  or loaf, or (elliptically) the festival of  Passover  (because no leaven was then used)

===== Definitions =====

  - greedily
  - sweetness
  - sweet
  - unfermented cake
  - Passover

===== Usage =====

unleaved (bread, cake), without leaven.
